  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Emerging endoscopic techniques are minimally invasive and can mimic the anatomic alterations
      achieved by surgical sleeve gastrectomy.

      The study hypothesis is if endoscopic sleeve gastroplasty is effective and useful in the
      treatment of patients with obesity
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The endoscopic sleeve gastroplasty method to perform endoluminal gastric reduction were by a
      cap-based flexible endoscopic suturing system. Post procedure care includes close follow-up
      by a nutritionist and a psychologist weekly.The outcome assessment included: change in body
      weight, percentage of loss of excess body weight and adverse effects
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
